column7:
Your review helps others learn about great local businesses.I am addicted to this place. The people so kind. The sevi e great. Love sitting outside!  Get there early.  They stay bizzie.
                                                                                                                      Location great. Close to walk to many Hotels.
                                                                                                                      I love wings, calypso muzik and pinya colada.
                                                                                                                      Just relax.

Late lunch or early dinner, either way, the service and food was amazing. The staff wore mask and are practicing social distancing. We had everything from the vegetable plate, rib combos to dessert and were very satisfied. My only regret is that we did not try a mixed drink.

Food was good and the service was fast :) the only thing is they will tell you that you dont need to make a reservation and just walk in and then when you get there you have to wait 20 mins or more. Just make a reservation before going and save some time.

Brought my wife here last Monday evening and even though it was a bit busy, we were greeted right away and promptly seated. Juan was our waiter. He was very friendly and made us feel right at home. We based our order on some solid recommendations that he made and everything was delicious! Cocktails were also very good. They had live music on the patio and it was an all around pleasant atmosphere right by the water. We would highly recommend!
My husband and I had a wonderful dinner here last night! Our server Ricardo was amazing! From now on we will definately ask to be seated in his section!

I hadn't returned to this place for years because I had a staple in my water and they were out of everything I tried to order. About five stars and years after that debacle, I revisited with a gift card in hand, and was glad I did. Price not an issue, I still gravitated towards the 39.95 prix fixe menu and basically had a 6oz. filet with all the fixins. There were four of us, and service was seamless offering to hold our sunglasses until after our meal lest we lose them in the meaty throw down about to ensue. The reason I'm carelessly blowin' a good five stars is because my filet was cooked precisely to temperature, and was sizzling madly in a pond of butter on my plate upon arrival. I enjoyed the flavor of everything that crossed my ravenous face hole. The place was immaculate, and the service slaughtered it. It may not be the best of the best steak in all of Tampaland, BUT if the service is like this all the time, then it's certainly tasty enough for me. Steak always tastes better when sprinkled heavily with flawless service.
Food was ok nothing special! Everytime, I eat here I leave with a Roma here ache. So I will no longer eat there. I really do not think there is any thing special about this place

Really excellent overall. We were seated fairly close to the kitchen and the level of organization and attention to detail exhibited there is evident in the final product. Many restaurants do not know how to cook a piece of salmon correctly, but mine was excellent, very moist and beautifully seasoned. We had some flatbread to begin with and that was very tasty as well. Service was good and our server was knowledgeable and pleasant, we will definitely be back!

I found Bahama Breeze on a recent Business Trip to Tampa.  The restaurant was near my hotel so I decided to stop in for dinner.  I had a great meal and enjoyed the wonderful weather seated outside overlooking the water, in JANUARY!  The food was excellent, the service great.  I will be back.

Been here twice and each time the service is AMAZING!  We went back after the first time because the service was so great.  So far I've liked everything I've eaten but the service is what really stands out.  There was a long wait on Valentine's Day and the waitress comped our appetizers without us asking or complaining.  She simply asked if we had a long wait and we said yes but said it was fine and she came back with an adjusted bill.  She also took one of the appetizers back (again without us asking) because she felt that it was a little skimpy.  Now THAT is service.  I will definitely be back.  Overall very good, nice ambiance, GREAT drinks (they're strong) and amazing staff.
